info.author: Dale Dupont
info.description: Packet sniffer command-line utility that filters for HTTP packets.                         The packet sniffer has filters for authentication request/response                         pairs to the Keycloak token endpoint that exchange access tokens.                         The sniffer may pretty-print or write JSON to either stdout or to an output file.                         The utility may either sniff live from a network interface or read from a packet capture file.
info.keywords: utility command-line debugging logging logger monitoring monitor network packet sniffer sniffing HTTP authentication token tokens filter
info.name: tokenTracer
info.summary: Keycloak token endpoint packet sniffer for HTTP request/response authentication tokens
